Partly cloudy- wind 0-5 mph- temp. 70 degrees F.
Public perception for Beaver Dam Lake.  Air temp. 65 degrees F.  Wind north-northeast 6 mph.
Sunny- t-80 degrees F- SW 8 mph- 1.5" rain 5/27-5/28.
Partly cloudy- temp. 76 degrees F- w-southwest 3 mph.  Rotenone treatment applied 1 week ago to Beaver Bay heights-misc.  Dead carp floating.
Temp 94 degrees F- clear skies- wind: east 6 mph- nor rain for 2 weeks-temp above 85 degrees F all week.
Partly sunny- no substantial rain in 3 weeks- temp 85 degrees F- wind S 5-10.
Clear skies- winds 3 mph west-southwest- much rain over weekend- temp 86 degrees F.
T-78 degrees F- winds 4 mph- no rain-hot! weather 1 wk.
T 68 degrees- winds 5-7 southwest- no rain-dry- clear skies.
Partly cloudy- winds 0-5 mph- temp-68 degrees F- algae-filamentous-green-approximately 4" of rain two days ago.
Partly cloudy- 58 degrees- winds east 10 mph.
Weather has been unusually cool.  High 30's nights- high 50 low 60 during the day.  Filamentous algae floating in lake.
Air temperature is 76 degrees- partly cloudy- winds SE @ 7 mph- algae bloom early July.
79 degrees- windy- partly sunny- filamentous algae.
82 degrees- lake calm- winds S 10 mph- partly sunny- filamentous and clumpy algae- blue/green algae on the lake shore.
Sunny- 70 degrees- winds- N 3 mph- filamentous algae.
Clear and sunny.  Winds 2 mph from the southwest.
Dissolved oxygen 9.28 mg/l.  Water temp=10.3 degrees C.  Clear and sunny.  Weather has been cooler than normal.  Spring has been extremely windy.
Dissolved oxygen is 9.01 mg/l.  Water temp=17.0 degrees C.  Clear and sunny.  Windy.
Sunny and 78 degrees.  Water calm.  Filamentous algae and globules.  Water temperature = 20.6 degrees C.- dissolved oxygen = 9.16 mg/liter.
Water 26.4 degrees C.  Weather partly sunny 98 degrees F.  Lots of boat traffic.
Sunny and 90 degrees.  Water temperature = 25.9 degrees C.  Dissolved oxygen = 6.34
Hot and humid all week.  A lot of boat traffic.  95 degrees and partly sunny.
Weather partly cloudy and cooler.  65 degrees.  Pretty rainy and cloudy.  Cool August.
Partly sunny- 80 degrees.  Filamentous algae- some blue green algae.
Dissolved oxygen = 5.37 mg/l. Temperature = 11.7 degrees C.  Partly cloudy and windy.
Hot sunny. Much boating activity due to lake days. Algae starting to form green globs.
Partly sunny cool windy. 64 degrees.  Some algae.
Unusually warm 50-60 degrees.  Water temp. 38 degrees. Dissolved oxygen 13.4 mg/l.
Partly cloudy- mid-60's. SW winds 5-10 mph.  Lake calm- like glass.  No boats in our area.

Partly sunny- mid-70's. SE winds 10-15 mph- lake rough- no white caps.  No rain for 1 week.  Two eagles and 2 loons- 1 boat in area.  Dissolved oxygen reading 8.73 mg/l.- water temperature 17.3 degrees C.
Temps in high 80's for last week.  Partly cloudy- 88 degrees.  Lots of rain for last week.
Received 6.5 inches of rain 7/20/99.  Hot and muggy- 90's.  Dissolved oxygen 13.24 mg/l.  Temperature 27.5 degrees C.
Hot and muggy last week- high 90's.  Partly sunny.  Lake 1.5 feet high.
Algae bloom on south end of lake.
70F light NE breeze- seen a few common cormorants- ducks and geese
lots of rain = flooding conditions=runoff=piers under water
lots of high water- some fine algae
80F- light west breeze- multi color algae on surface
cluster algae on surface- some fisherman out- cormorants all over
60F light W wind- small light algae- cormorants-american white pelicans
65F- calm some cluster algae- some large- some small- some fishermen out
80F S wind 10-15mph- some light algae- fine stuff- lots of birds on lake
50F light W Breeze- algae is very light
Heavy rain in last 12 hours- small waves- partly cloudy- blue-green algae 'Fanny' bloom (per Sefton)
Hot- sunny- blue-green algae bloom- fish kill affecting mostly small fish- e.g.- 4-5" walleye- small bluegill- etc.
pleasure boats all over- some gulls on lake
Partly cloudy- heavy rain in last 24 hours- some algae- mid 70's.
lots of gulls- local mallards- cormorants- several fishermen
Day is P/C to sunny- lt. wind from SW- 2 boats on big lake fishing- no vegetation here
Breezy.  SE winds. Partly Sunny.  Pelicans- few cormorants and gulls.
NE wind- cloudy- moderate algae bloom- no rain in last 2 weeks.  Lake is low.
Sunny- calm- hot (90)- blue-green algae.  Heavy rain (5" + ) 5 days ago.  Unusual number of gulls up and down the lake but no obvious fish kill.  Pelicans have left.
90 Degrees- SW wind- sunny- algae bloom but no blue-green algae- fishing has been good for panfish- bass and catfish.
Sunny- warm- very breezy.  No fishermen out.
light NE breeze- sunny- no algae- a few ducks- cormorants and pelicans- about 60 degrees F- strong NW wind the day before.
Partly sunny- W wind- choppy- no major algae bloom this year...very strange- no readings in June due to flooding conditions.
Sunny- NE wind 5-7mph- a few fisherman- no serious algae bloom so far this year.
No vegetation- a few cormorants- a few fishermen- no algae- light SE breeze.
No vegatation.  Light green fuzzy algae.  Very few birds.  A few fishing boats.
Sunny- SW breeze- slight chop- few fishermen- ducks- cormorants- gulls.  Not much alge and no major algae bloom so far this year.
Mostly sunny- calm- no algae and water is very clear.  Pelicans- ducks- cormorants.  A few fishermen.
Sunny- warm- light wind.  Several fishermen.  Fishing has been very poor all summer.  No pelicans- only a couple of cormorants.  Lake is 'pickle' green but no floating algae.
blue wing teal.  canada geese.  cormorants
Sunny- SW breeze- very few fishermen- algae forming- 80 degrees
NW breeze- mostly sunny- no fishermen- moderate algae bloom
Mostly sunny- light chop- no fishermen- moderate algae
I did not see any amount of pelicans- cormarants- ducks or geese.  Lots of pleasure boats and several fishermen.  75*- east wind 10 mph- sunny.
Mostly sunny.  Good number of fishermen- pelicans- slight algae bloom- 75- S wind 5mph- slight chop.
Cloudy- hot- a few fishermen- a number of recreational boaters- plenty of ducks- gulls- cormorants- and pelicans.  SW breeze- choppy.
Sunny- calm- lots of pelicans and cormorants.  Only a couple of fishermen.
Sunny- 70 degrees- light norht wind- lot of pelicans- some cormorants- a few fishermen
Sunny- light NE wind- 75 degrees- lake is low and no rain in weeks.  No fishermen except commercial crew.  A few pelicans and cormorants.  Very mild algae bloom.
Sunny 74- light NW breeze- algal bloom- only 2 boats on the lake- lots of pelicans on north end- a few cormorants.
Sunny- NE wind 5-10- 61 Degrees- no fishermen- no pelicans- lots of gulls- high winds 15-20 nw previous 2 days.
75- Sunny- light south breeze- only a few fishermen- 100-s of pelicans but only a few cormorants.
74- Cloudy- 1.3 inches rain in the last 4 days.
Samples taken with Rachel Sabre- Sunny- wind 8-10 mph.
Sunny- dry- 70 degrees- light NE breeze- pelicans are gone- a few goldeneye in mid-lake- several fishermen but fishing has been very bad all summer and has now continued into fall.
Cloudy- 70- light NW breeze- blue-green algae forming along east shore of main basin.  Much better north of the Skunk islands.
Mostly sunny- low 70s- green but no floating algae- calm
Strong winds previous 48 hours so the lake is not quite a clear as it is normally.  Sunny with a light breeze.

Sunny with light breeze.  Some algae and a few weeds in the basin but many bays are choked.  Mostly Curly Leaf Pondweed but some sago in the bays.  Much better conditions than further north in the narrows.

Sunny- most of the weeds- primarily curley-leafed pondweed- have died back.  Lot of algae.   Very few pelicans and cormorants compared to previous years.  Not much carp action being reported around the lake.

10-15mph w/nw winds gusting to 25-30 Sat- Sun- Mon.  Cloudy- 70degrees today. lt. nw wind.  heavy concentrations of algae in some areas of the lake.  About 10 boats fishing (probably perch).  Not many pelicans or cormorants.
Sunny.  LT NE wind.  Heavy Algae bloom.
80 degrees- partly sunny.  SW winds about 10mph.  Lite algae bloom- water mostly clear- shallow bays very weedy (mostly CLP).  Only saw several fishermen out.
Sunny- west wind approx. 15- 80 degrees- slight algae bloom- CLP is dying back but still thick in the bays.  Some pelicans but did not see any cormorants.
88 degrees- calm wind- mostly cloudy.  Only 1 or 2 fishermen out.
1.5 to 2.0 inches of rain in the last week.  Calm- partly sunny- 80 degrees.  Only 4 or 5 boats out.

Partly cloudy.  NE wind around 8.  Just over 1" of rain in the last 24 hours.  Over 300 pelicans and cormorants on High Island- most I've ever seen there.  Lake is still high and dam is running at 397cfs.  Some matted CLP but not as bad as 2 previous years.
Partly sunny- light south breeze- 70 degrees.  Lots of perch fishermen and the most cormorants and pelicans that I've ever seen on the lake and schools of small ( 6"- 8") buffalo everywhere.
80 degrees- light NE wind.  About 1.5 inches of rain in last 48 hours.  Hundreds of cormorants and pelicans.  Commercial fishermen up in Rakes bay.  Only 2 recreational fishermen out.
Sunny 70 degrees.  E wind 10 - 15.  Hundreds of pelicans but few cormorants.  Several fishermen in main basin.
Cloudy.  70 ENE wind 5 - 10.  2 fishing boats out.  Spotty algae blooms mostly in the main basin and southern part of the narrows.  3 inches of rain in the last 4 days. Lake is a little high.
72 degrees- light variable wind- partly sunny.  1.1 inches of rain four days ago.  2 or 3  fishing boats out.
70 degrees.  Lite SE wind.  Mostly cloudy.  Approx 8 inches rain in last 7 days.  Lake approx. 1' high.
Overcast. 57degrees. E wind 10-20 Gusts to 30.  1.5" rain in last 5 days
Sunny- 75 degrees and calm.  Over 1" of rain in the last 48 hours.  Algae buildup along west shore in the main basin
80 degrees.  Light wind- partly cloudy.  2.25" of rain in the last week.  2 fishermen out.
70 degrees- mostly cloudy- wind SE 9.  Several fishermen.  Hundreds of white pelicans.  No rain in the last 5 days.
Sunny-  windy.  Several fishermen.  Less pelicans and cormorants than last year.  2-3 inches of rain 3 days ago.

column1: PHOSPHOROUS:  Sample was submitted to Beaver Dam Waste Water Utility for analysis.  BDWWU is now a certified lab.  Total Phosphorous = 0.112 mg/l.  Sample collected with an integrated sampler at 1-3'

column2: Partly sunny- 71 degrees- NW wind 5-10.  USGS recorded .75 inches of rain over the last 4 days.  No fishermen spotted.  Very few pelicans and cormorants on the water.  Most of the curly leaf pond weed- which was abundant on the west side and especially in the bays- has almost disappeared.

75 degrees- sunny- SE wind 10- 2 fishing boats out.  Total of 1.2 inches of rain recorded by USGS over last 6 days.  No serious algae blooms so far this summer.  Many reports of large schools of minnows along the shoreline.
Sunny.  75 Degrees.  Calm.  Only 2 fishing boats.
